          "id": "53ea912acbbf_6",
          "href": null,
          "name": "5b3e",
          "text": "Below is a recording of the keynote presentation I gave at the Travel to Tomorrow Summit organised by Visit Flanders in Bruges, on September 12th and 13th, 2019.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "53ea912acbbf_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "4e1f",
          "text": "The presentation explores how climate change now urges a fundamental redesign of the human presence and impact on Earth, and how tourism with its cross-sectorial and global-local impact could be turned from being a growing problem into a solution for regional regeneration and the improvement of local climate resilience.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "53ea912acbbf_8",
          "href": null,
          "name": "390a",
          "text": "This presentation is somewhat challenging to people in the industry and climate activists alike, and yet, I firmly belief that “we are all crew own spaceship Earth” and we will have to work together to achieve the rapid transition now needed in the time left.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
